  "texts": [
    "Yamin et al. [16] introduced an innovative system designed to address the inefficiencies in conducting cyber-security exercises within cyber ranges after conducting a detailed study on unclassified cyber-ranges [17].",
    "It acknowledges the complexity and resource-intensive nature of current practices, which often fail to replicate the dynamic nature of real-world systems.",
    "To counter this, the authors introduced an automated approach using modeldriven methods to streamline the cyber-security exercise life cycle.",
    "Their system models the roles of various teams such as White, Green, Red, and Blue, and generates automation artifacts to execute these functions autonomously, adding realism to the exercises.",
    "The system was evaluated through case studies involving national-level competitions and university classes in Norway, demonstrating its ability to rapidly create complex infrastructures and improve participant skills."
